Argentine Stock Movers: Banco Hipotecario, Banco Macro, Tenaris

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-08-31T15:12:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/argentine-stock-movers-banco-hipotecario-banco-macro-tenaris.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 10:48 a.m. New York time.  The Merval Index increased 0.6 percent to 2,978.35.  Banks rose in line with emerging-market stocks on
speculation the Federal Reserve may announce measures to shore
up the U.S. economy next month.  Banco Hipotecario SA (BHIP AF) gained 2 percent to 2.02
pesos.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  , Argentina’s largest lender by
market value, advanced 0.8 percent to 12.10 pesos.  Tenaris SA (TEN)   added 1.8 percent to 73.30 pesos. The
world’s largest producer of steel tubes used in the petroleum
industry gained after U.S. factory orders rose faster than
economist forecasts in July.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in Buenos Aires at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  